  "transcript": {
    "language": "en",
    "is_generated": true,
    "segments": [
      {
        "start": 0.2,
        "duration": 5.4,
        "text": "This is Joshua Tree National Park and it"
      },
      {
        "start": 2.7,
        "duration": 5.0,
        "text": "is a true desert climate. What does that"
      },
      {
        "start": 5.5,
        "duration": 3.9,
        "text": "mean? Well, for one, it means it gets"
      },
      {
        "start": 7.7,
        "duration": 4.4,
        "text": "very little rain over here, only about"
      },
      {
        "start": 9.4,
        "duration": 4.9,
        "text": "four to five inches in an entire year."
      },
      {
        "start": 12.1,
        "duration": 4.7,
        "text": "And the air is extremely dry, which"
      },
      {
        "start": 14.3,
        "duration": 4.6,
        "text": "causes the land to heat up very quickly"
      },
      {
        "start": 16.8,
        "duration": 4.2,
        "text": "during the day and cool down very"
      },
      {
        "start": 19.0,
        "duration": 3.8,
        "text": "quickly at night. So, the daily"
      },
      {
        "start": 21.0,
        "duration": 5.4,
        "text": "temperatures can sometimes differ by"
      },
      {
        "start": 22.7,
        "duration": 8.5,
        "text": "about 50° Fahrenheit or even more. And"
      },
      {
        "start": 26.4,
        "duration": 7.0,
        "text": "yet some organisms live here just fine."
      },
      {
        "start": 31.2,
        "duration": 4.6,
        "text": "For example, Joshua trees grow tall in"
      },
      {
        "start": 33.4,
        "duration": 4.7,
        "text": "the desert. We have kangaroo rats that"
      },
      {
        "start": 35.8,
        "duration": 5.4,
        "text": "survive without ever drinking liquid"
      },
      {
        "start": 38.2,
        "duration": 6.4,
        "text": "waters. And Chakala lizards can rest"
      },
      {
        "start": 41.1,
        "duration": 6.6,
        "text": "just fine on sunwarmmed rocks. But many"
      },
      {
        "start": 44.6,
        "duration": 6.1,
        "text": "organisms couldn't survive here at all."
      },
      {
        "start": 47.8,
        "duration": 5.5,
        "text": "So that begs the question, why can some"
      },
      {
        "start": 50.6,
        "duration": 6.2,
        "text": "organisms live in a particular place"
      },
      {
        "start": 53.3,
        "duration": 6.0,
        "text": "while others can't? The answer has to do"
      },
      {
        "start": 56.9,
        "duration": 5.9,
        "text": "with the conditions and resources"
      },
      {
        "start": 59.3,
        "duration": 6.4,
        "text": "available in the environment. Okay, what"
      },
      {
        "start": 62.8,
        "duration": 5.2,
        "text": "do I mean by that? Every living thing"
      },
      {
        "start": 65.7,
        "duration": 5.1,
        "text": "from the largest plants and animals to"
      },
      {
        "start": 68.0,
        "duration": 5.6,
        "text": "the smallest microorganisms"
      },
      {
        "start": 70.8,
        "duration": 6.2,
        "text": "need certain things, certain resources"
      },
      {
        "start": 73.6,
        "duration": 6.2,
        "text": "to survive. Right now those resources"
      },
      {
        "start": 77.0,
        "duration": 4.5,
        "text": "can come from the living parts of the"
      },
      {
        "start": 79.8,
        "duration": 4.4,
        "text": "environment which we call the biotic"
      },
      {
        "start": 81.5,
        "duration": 5.0,
        "text": "factors and the non-living parts of the"
      },
      {
        "start": 84.2,
        "duration": 5.4,
        "text": "environment which we call the abiotic"
      },
      {
        "start": 86.6,
        "duration": 5.8,
        "text": "factors. It's the combination of these"
      },
      {
        "start": 89.6,
        "duration": 4.7,
        "text": "biotic and abiotic factors that decide"
      },
      {
        "start": 92.3,
        "duration": 4.9,
        "text": "which organisms can live in a particular"
      },
      {
        "start": 94.3,
        "duration": 5.2,
        "text": "environment and which can't. So let's"
      },
      {
        "start": 97.2,
        "duration": 4.8,
        "text": "talk about this in more detail. What are"
      },
      {
        "start": 99.5,
        "duration": 4.2,
        "text": "biotic factors? The biotic factors"
      },
      {
